SASS Installation Steps for Windows:

1. Downloaded Node.js LTS version from nodejs.org
2. Ran the Windows installer (.msi) with default settings
3. Verified Node.js installation: node --version (showed v20.x.x)
4. Verified npm installation: npm --version (showed 10.x.x)
5. Installed SASS globally: npm install -g sass
6. Verified SASS installation: sass --version (showed 1.77.4)
7. Tested compilation by creating test.scss and running: sass test.scss test.css

Installation successful and ready for SASS/SCSS development.